2026-02-15 00:56:02,001 - INFO -    Strategy: The codebase implements a comprehensive team-based permission system with role hierarchy. Key components include: 1) TeamDashboardPage for team management, 2) InviteMemberModal for inviting members with specific roles, 3) RemoveMemberButton for member removal with permission checks, 4) TeamSwitcher for switching between teams, 5) TEAM_PERMISSIONS constants defining granular permissions (ACCESS_DASHBOARD, INVITE_MEMBERS, REMOVE_MEMBERS, CREATE_COMPONENTS, EDIT_COMPONENTS), 6) SYSTEM_ROLES_ENUM for role hierarchy (Owner, Admin, Member), 7) hasTeamPermission and requireTeamPermission utility functions for permission validation. The system uses Drizzle ORM relations (teamRelations, teamMembershipRelations, teamRoleRelations) to model team-member-role relationships, and implements server actions like inviteUserAction, acceptInvitationAction, removeTeamMemberAction with permission checks.
